text: 12 Super Exitos is a compilation album by Mexican-American Tejano pop singer, Selena. The album sold more than 500,000 copies in the United States, being certified Gold by the RIAA. == Track listing == # "Si Una Vez" # "La Llamada" # "No debes Jugar" # "Las Cadenas" # "Techno Cumbia" # "Tú Robaste Mi Corazón" (with Emilio Navaira) # "Bidi Bidi Bom Bom" # "No Quiero Saber" # "La Carcacha" # "Missing My Baby" # "Como La Flor" # "Qué Creías" == Certifications and sales == Country Certification Sales United States Gold 500,000+ == References == Category:1994 albums Category:Selena albums Category:Compilation albums
